               and rosette-like rolls of white flour sent the name Vienna around the world? Were these boulevards ever gay at night with lights
               and music from every restaurant? Where is the bright-faced populace that flocked on
               Sundays to Wiener Wald\oindex{Wien@\textbf{Wien}!Wienerwald@\textbf{Wienerwald}|pw} at the first excuse for
               Spring? Is Kreisler\pwindex{Kreisler, Fritz@\textsc{Kreisler, Fritz} (2.\,2.\,1875 Wien – 29.\,1.\,1962 New York City), \emph{Komponist, Pianist}|pw}’s »Caprice Viennoise\pwindex{Kreisler, Fritz@\textsc{Kreisler, Fritz} (2.\,2.\,1875 Wien – 29.\,1.\,1962 New York City), \emph{Komponist, Pianist}!Caprice Viennois1910@\strich\emph{Caprice Viennois} {[}1910{]}|pw}\pwindex{Kreisler, Fritz@\textsc{Kreisler, Fritz} (2.\,2.\,1875 Wien – 29.\,1.\,1962 New York City), \emph{Komponist, Pianist}!Caprice Viennois1910@\strich\emph{Caprice Viennois} {[}1910{]}|pw}« mere fancy? And when you have studied the
               faces in the city of to-day you wonder most of all, was there ever a Vienna such as Dr. Arthur
