           \pstart
           \sindex[question]{@!@}\introOben{}»\introOben{}The solution of the Jewish Problem,« \introOben{}said Schnitzler\introOben{} »is one which each individual must find for himself.
                  \label{L-I028-1v}\label{L-I028-1h}\sindex[question]{@!@}There
               is no general solution. Zionism does not seem to me to be a solution at all. It seems
               to me too much actuated by sudden impulses, by resentment, by a mere desire to escape
               from one’s environment and scarcely ever to spring from a well-reasoned decision.
               This does not prevent me from admiring Zionism. I admire people who can reach out so
               high and dream so splendidly, but they will never convince me.\pend
           \pstart
           \sindex[question]{@!@}I need hardly point out that the Zionist plays
               actively into the hands of the anti-Semite. He confesses to a weakness in our
               position which my mind does not exist. My parents come from Hungary, but my \label{K_I028-44v}\edtext{desire takes me back neither to Hungary}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{desire … Hungary}}}\Cendnote{\textnormal{$\triangleright$\myrangeref{I066_L_ungarnv}{I066_L_ungarnh}}}}\label{K_I028-44h}{ }nor Palestine\oindex{Palaestina@\textbf{Palästina}|pw}. I am rooted here in Vienna, my
               home and the home of my youth. I have grown up identifying myself with the highly
               individual culture. I am part of it, and it is part of me. Why should I leave this
               country because a few ignorant and illbred fools of anti-Semites tell me I do not
               belong here?\pend
           \pstart
           \sindex[question]{@!@}\introOben{}»\introOben{}Do I believe that there is a basic individual Jewish
               character apart from certain traits which environment has forced upon it\substVorne{}\textsuperscript{.}\substDazwischen{}?\substHinten{} That is a difficult question\textcolor{gray}{;} yet I should if anything be
               inclined to a negative \label{T_I028-1234v}\edtext{answer.}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{answer.}}}\Aendnote{\textnormal{answer}}}\label{T_I028-1234h} I do not
               believe that the Jew is essentially spiritually different or that there is a
               difference of spiritual rhythm between him \label{T_I028-113v}\edtext{and}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{and}}}\Aendnote{\textnormal{a}}}\label{T_I028-113h} the gentile. The attitude of the world towards him
               has produced certain psychological modifications. Take away this attitude, and those
               modifications will \substVorne{}\textsuperscript{vanish. I believe every \textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×}\-\textcolor{gray}{×} of jewish parentage even of}{\allowbreak}\substDazwischen{}vanish. I believe that if a child of jewish parentage, even
                     of\substHinten{} the humblest sort, were to be taken to another country, kept in ignorance of
               its origin if that origin were also kept from its associates, that this child would
               grow up absolutely unconscious of a difference between itself and its playmates,
               except perhaps that it might develop and become{\pb} aware of a keener and quicker
               brain.\pend
           \pstart
           \label{TT114-4v}\edtext{I am however compelled to admit that
               there is a sort of Freemasonary between Jews. We unconsciously feel our way to one
               another more quickly than we do to gentiles. There is a readier unspoken
               understanding. But how far this implies an actual being different on our part I
               hesitate to say.}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{I … say.}}}\Cendnote{\textnormal{Absatz fehlt im
                  Erstdruck}}}\label{TT114-4h}\pend
           \pstart
           \sindex[question]{@!@}Why anti-Semitism has gained so much strength
               recently? I think it has to do with the general state the world is in at present.
               Remember that a wave of hate has swept over the peoples of the \substVorne{}\textsuperscript{world}\substDazwischen{}earth\substHinten{}, and that hate is a very real deep rooted instinct, which must have its vent
               once it is aroused. Some object must be found for it, and it is therefore not
               unnaturally, that it concentrates on a section of the community that enjoys a certain
               traditional privilege of persecution, a section of the community\introOben{},\introOben{} moreover\introOben{},\introOben{} which for some reason or other is
               weakened by an excessive objectivity and by a certain inclination to self analysis,
               and is therefore perhaps a readier victim.\pend
           \pstart
           \sindex[question]{@!@}Do I think that the Jews are a creative people?
               I must unhesitatingly answer that I do. Look at the names that we can show within a
               short space of time. \label{TT114-5v}\edtext{In music Richard Strauss\pwindex{Strauss, Richard@\textsc{Strauss, Richard} (11.\,6.\,1864 München – 8.\,9.\,1949 Garmisch-Partenkirchen), \emph{Theaterleiter, Komponist, Dirigent}|pw} and Gustav Mahler\pwindex{Mahler, Gustav@\textsc{Mahler, Gustav} (7.\,7.\,1860 Kaliště – 18.\,5.\,1911 Wien), \emph{Theaterleiter, Komponist, Dirigent}|pw}. In painting Max
                  Liebermann\pwindex{Liebermann, Max@\textsc{Liebermann, Max} (20.\,7.\,1847 Berlin – 8.\,2.\,1935 ebd.), \emph{Maler}|pw}, in literature a whole host of names.}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{In … names.}}}\Cendnote{\textnormal{Das fehlt im Erstdruck, weil Strauss\pwindex{Strauss, Richard@\textsc{Strauss, Richard} (11.\,6.\,1864 München – 8.\,9.\,1949 Garmisch-Partenkirchen), \emph{Theaterleiter, Komponist, Dirigent}|pwk} kein Jude war. Oberhalb von Strauss\pwindex{Strauss, Richard@\textsc{Strauss, Richard} (11.\,6.\,1864 München – 8.\,9.\,1949 Garmisch-Partenkirchen), \emph{Theaterleiter, Komponist, Dirigent}|pwk} ein unentziffertes handschriftliches Wort, wahrscheinlich von Schnitzler, eben dies bemängelnd.}}}\label{TT114-5h} More
               than that I believe we are on the verge of great Jewish renaissance. \label{K_I028-4v}\edtext{What the artistic}{\lemma{\textnormal{\emph{What the artistic}}}\Cendnote{\textnormal{Ab hier ist der Text handschriftlich geschrieben.}}}\label{K_I028-4h}
               message is that Judaism has to deliver I do not{\pb} know, but there is a promise of
               something in the air. Any man with a feeling for these things must become aware of
               it.\pend
